Operational note: GreyNOC CryptoProbe performs ACTIVE network probing — it
completes TLS handshakes against the targets it is pointed at. It is for
AUTHORIZED TESTING ONLY. The operator is solely responsible for ensuring they
have explicit permission to probe any target. The tool refuses to run active
probes without a recorded authorization identifier (operator/ticket) or an
authorizing scope file, and rate-limits by default. It performs handshake
negotiation and certificate inspection only — no exploitation, no
denial-of-service, no authentication attacks.

